product_name: LancomeLe Stylo Waterproof Long-Lasting Eyeliner Pencil
summary: SummaryLancôme Le Stylo Eyeliner Pencil is a creamy, waterproof eyeliner that glides on for seamless application on both the lash line and waterline.
details: DetailsFeaturesThis versatile eye pencil smoothly glides onto lash line for precise application and intense pigmented color that won't budge or flake.xWith a buttery texture, Le Stylo allows for seamless blending and smudging with its built-in smudger that sets to a long-lasting waterproof formula when dry.Available in two impactful finishes, matte and metallic in multiple dramatic shades.BenefitsLong-wearingWaterproofCreamy FormulaItem 2587429How To UseApply eyeliner directly on eyelid as close to the lash line as possible. Use on both top and bottom lashes for a natural makeup or a bold makeup look.For Smudging Application:Apply eyeliner pencil directly onto eyelid as close to the lash line as possible.Use included smudging tool to smudge product and feather out for light to intense pigment.Use on both top and bottom lashes for medium-to-bold smokey eye and gradient makeup looks, or as a eyeshadow base.IngredientsCI 77499 / Iron Oxides, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Synthetic Wax, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Hydrogenated Poly (C6-14 Olefin), Hydrogenated Polydecene, Mica, Silica Silylate, Polybutene, CI 77266 / Black 2, CI 77510 / Ferric Ammonium Ferrocyanide, Copernicia Cerifera Cera / Carnauba Wax, Ethylene/Propylene Copolymer, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Chocolate Eyeliner Eyes
reviews.comments: I purchased Lancôme's Chocolat color eyeliner.  Its color is richly pigmented, soft creamy, glides on effortlessly and sets quickly.  My sensitive eyes have a tendency to water with any kind of eyeliner!  I noticed, 'once this particular eyeliner dries down' my eyes stop watering making it comfortable to wear rain or shine.  Thank you Lancôme!  Thank you Ulta!

reviews.headline: Disappointed.....
reviews.comments: Did not work at all on my waterline! And too expensive

reviews.headline: I had high hopes for this eyeliner
reviews.comments: Does not blend well

reviews.headline: Love this
reviews.comments: I used to use a brand that rhymes with Barry Lay and they stopped making the eyeliner I liked (they did that with many products --- took a good item and just discontinued it) so I sought a replacement. I really like this Lancôme product. It's not runny and smudgy but it's firm enough to apply easily. I do not like liquid eyeliner so this is my choice. I  love the array of colors available. I have bluey-green eyes and the slate grey color works well as does the metallic deep green. I can't wear black eyeliner - it washes me out. I have made this my #1 fave eyeliner now and Barry May can keep theirs!

reviews.headline: Finally something that stays put in the heat!
reviews.comments: I want to give this eyeliner 5 stars because it's the first eyeliner I've found in 15 years that with my oily skin doesn't end up melting under my eyes at the end of the day, no matter the heat. That's HUGE for me. However, I have to take one off for the applicator. Not being able to sharpen it in anyway means I can never get as nice and precise a line as I could if it were fresh and pointed. If they made this as an actual pencil-pencil I'd never stop raving about it.

reviews.headline: Perfect for waterline!
reviews.comments: I wanted a smudge proof pencil for the waterline. After reading reviews recommending this pencil, I purchased Le Stylo. It is indeed smudge proof and waterproof. I have both the black and matte brown pencils

reviews.headline: Great purchase, it glides on.
reviews.comments: I will continue to purchase the eyeliner, it's amazing, lasts all day in until cleaned off at the end of the day.

reviews.headline: I love this brand
reviews.comments: It is the second color I have  bought, it stays true on my eyelids for a long time

reviews.headline: No

reviews.headline: It's giving early 2010s but in a GOOD way
reviews.comments:
I used to wear black eyeliner with a bit of glitter every day in my early 20s, and recently I wanted to do it again when I feel fancy about my makeup, because, to be honest, sometimes we are just tired of the "clean beauty" makeup. It's the idea of "too much restriction" and a hint of "judgment" from the clean beauty that makes me feel it's enough. I want to have some fun with my makeup to feel like myself again. 
Although the glitter eyeliner is hard to find these days, I found the Lancome this one in "Noir Oynx" is perfect and retro after tried a couple of other brands. I think the glitters in the pencil actually make my eyes pop more bcoz I have hooded eyes, while the other matte ones just makes my eyes look smaller or more dull. Overall, great product if you want to splurge to have some fun!

reviews.headline: I wouldn't buy this again
reviews.comments: This eyeliner did not last all day not worth the money cheaper ones I have bought have last longer.  just bought the same. Just didn't work for me

reviews.headline: Thee Best Eyeliner Ever!!!
reviews.comments: I absolutely love this eyeliner!  I have used this eyeliner for over 30 years…

reviews.headline: It's ok but...
reviews.comments: I really wanted to love this but it's just ok. It did stay on most of the day but there was some under my eyes and I had to keep checking it throughout the day. It is really pigmented and that makes it look like most of it has stayed put. I have sensitive eyes when it comes to eyeliner and this didn't irritate me at all.  For the price I probably won't buy it again. I can get the same at half the price.

reviews.headline: Excellent pencil liner
reviews.comments: This works great for tight lining and general eye liner.  It goes on smooth, doesn't fade and is waterproof.  I buy two at a time because I hate to run out.

reviews.headline: Best eyeliner!
reviews.comments: This is the best eyeliner I've ever used. My eyes water a good bit so I needed something waterproof. It goes on easy and can layer to make it darker. I've been asked what kind of eyeliner I use and the ladies bought it for themselves and love it! The only complaint I have is that there's no way to tell how much is left, so I try to make sure I always have another one available in case I run out while putting on my makeup.

reviews.headline: Didn't like it but maybe you will
reviews.comments: I've been trying to make this work for me as I really wanted to start doing a smudged eyeliner look but the sponge part of these are really dry. The pencil itself glides well but blending it can be a little hard. Maybe it just wasnt for me.

reviews.headline: I found it!  Perfect eyeliner
reviews.comments: I have tried almost every brand of gel eyeliner. For the longest time I couldn't settle on just one. I bought every price point. This one from Lancome was on sale so of course I tried it. This one is the best! It glides on smooth, goes on thin or thick. It stays all day, and doesn't smear. Ive had it for a month and it hasn't ran out. I don't usually use Lancome, So happy I found the one that works.

reviews.headline: Sutley enhances the eye and waterproof.
reviews.comments: Enhanced my eye color, just enough to get a second glance from hubby!

reviews.headline: THE WORST.
reviews.comments: If I could rate 0 I would. It barely stays on and it breaks very easily. I spent so much money when I could've spent a lot cheaper for the same quality.

reviews.headline: Great. Stays put
reviews.comments: Finally a liner I can use on the bottom. Chocolate matte color is perfect for my light eyes.

faceoff_positive.comments: I will not use any other type of eyeliner. My daughter only liked liquid until I made her try this one, now this is all she uses as well. I even got her the Idôle set of mascara/liquid eyeliner combo, but when she saw the amount of control the le stylo gave her, there was no going back.
faceoff_positive.headline: A MUST HAVE!

faceoff_negative.comments: I've used artliner for years. Worried smoke is going away. Have all colors and limited edition ones.  Running out. I Like a precise line.  Thought I'd try Le Stylo since more colors. First, it broke off midway thru using, so I tried a lighter touch.  Still broke.  Second, it smudged and did not stay on even in first few hours.  Use your setting spray too.  Use your le base pro. Use the eye base. Use your foundation.  Use your mascara.  Didn't work😥
faceoff_negative.headline: Disappointed
